playerText: TM: Hey I see your ticket ?

npcText: He is averagely built man with wild, uncouth hair and a face that hasn't felt the touch of a razor in weeks.

playerText: I'm sorry could you please repeat that ?
Would you like some time alone. Sir ?

npcText: ...I don't want to think about it
Does it matter ? They're all dead anyways, thanks to me.
... I watched them die. We were surrounded. I didn't even help. I just hid, like a coward.

playerText: Thats not cowardly, I would have done the same.
npcText: But I should have died with them or helped. I didn't do anything. My best friend died in front of my eyes.
It should have been me... He has a wife... and kids... I don't have anything. I should just die.

playerText: I don't think he would have wanted that. At least someone can tell his family what happened. ?
npcText: His kids will never see him again.

playerText: You could tell them about him. This train goes back into town. I just need the ticket.
Well would you like to talk about it ?
Aw come on. Let it out dude. I don't have all day.
npcText: ...Just take it and leave me alone

playerText: Sir the train can't leave until I check your ticket
If you don't comply I will have to use force. Your ticket please. Else leave the train.

npcText: Press anywhere after clipping to confirm.
